# Antigravity UI & Frontend Design Guidelines

## Scope — read this first

This rule is **intentionally NOT global**. It only applies to public-facing,
non-ERP-admin screens — currently the auth/login screens
(`src/app/(auth)/**`), and any future public marketing/landing pages
(`src/app/(public)/**`, `src/app/(marketing)/**`).

**Do NOT apply this aesthetic to:**
- Any ERP admin/workspace screen (lists, record forms, child dialogs, drawers,
  dashboards, reports, HR/DMS/Finance/Party Master/etc. modules)
- Anything governed by `erp-global-list-ui-standard.mdc`,
  `erp-record-workspace-form-standard.mdc`, `erp-child-dialog-form-standard.mdc`,
  `erp-workspace-tabs-standard.mdc`, or any other `erp-*-standard.mdc` rule

Those ERP rules are deliberately flat, dense, and low-motion for data-heavy
back-office use, and they take precedence over this file wherever they
overlap. If a task touches both a public screen and an ERP screen, follow
this rule only for the public screen's portion of the work.

When in doubt about whether a file is in scope, check whether it sits under
an ERP module route (`/admin/**`, `/dms/**`, `/hr/**`, workspace tabs) — if
so, this rule does not apply.

---

## Design Direction

Avoid safe, generic, flat layouts. Commit to spatial depth, glassmorphism,
weightlessness, and heavy motion.

## Motion & Weightlessness

Never snap state changes instantly. All UI interactions must have smooth
transitions. Use GSAP (and ScrollTrigger) to animate elements floating gently
into view along the Y-axis.

## Spatial Depth & Glassmorphism

Do not use flat borders. Use layered, soft, diffused drop-shadows (e.g.,
`box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)`). Apply subtle translucency and
background blurs (`backdrop-filter: blur(12px)`) for a premium glassy feel.
Use 3D CSS transforms like `rotateX` and `perspective` on cards and grids to
create Z-axis layering.

## Typography

Never use generic fonts like Arial or Inter. Choose distinctive display
fonts paired with refined body fonts from Google Fonts. Vary font weights at
extremes (e.g., 200 vs 800) rather than subtle steps.

## Details & Atmosphere

Do not default to solid background colors. Use gradient meshes, geometric
patterns, layered transparencies, and dramatic lighting to create atmosphere.

---

## Implementation Notes

- **GSAP is not currently installed** in this project (`package.json` has no
  `gsap` dependency). Install it (`npm install gsap`) before using
  ScrollTrigger-based float-in animations on an in-scope page.
- Keep bundle-size and accessibility in mind: respect
  `prefers-reduced-motion` and provide a non-animated fallback for users who
  have it enabled.
- This rule is `alwaysApply: false` and glob-scoped — attach it manually (or
  rely on the glob match) when working on an in-scope public/auth screen. It
  will not be auto-injected into ERP admin module work.
